{
  "nodes": [
    {
      "id": "thesis",
      "type": "file",
      "file": "10 - Patterns and Theses/Thesis - Eyewitness Divergence in Transient Aerial Events.md",
      "x": -150,
      "y": -540,
      "width": 520,
      "height": 300,
      "color": "1"
    },
    {
      "id": "legend",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Eyewitness divergence\n\nMultiple eyewitnesses to the same transient aerial event routinely produce materially different descriptions of size, shape, distance, and behavior.\n\nThis ==does not require any unusual property of the object==; it matches the cognitive-psychology and aviation-safety literature on eyewitness reliability.\n\nThe 2023-09 LiDAR Convoy is the cleanest example in the collection.",
      "x": -900,
      "y": -540,
      "width": 600,
      "height": 420,
      "color": "2"
    },
    {
      "id": "inc-lidar",
      "type": "file",
      "file": "03 - Incidents/Incident - 2023-09 LiDAR Convoy.md",
      "x": -150,
      "y": -120,
      "width": 520,
      "height": 260,
      "color": "5"
    },
    {
      "id": "loc",
      "type": "file",
      "file": "05 - Locations/Location - CONUS LiDAR Test Site.md",
      "x": 480,
      "y": -90,
      "width": 360,
      "height": 180,
      "color": "6"
    },
    {
      "id": "phenom",
      "type": "file",
      "file": "09 - Phenomenology/Phenom - Linear Object with Bright Light.md",
      "x": 480,
      "y": 140,
      "width": 360,
      "height": 180,
