    },
    {
      "id": "wA",
      "type": "file",
      "file": "08 - Witnesses/Witness - LiDAR Test Convoy Witness A.md",
      "x": -700,
      "y": 240,
      "width": 380,
      "height": 200,
      "color": "4"
    },
    {
      "id": "srcA",
      "type": "file",
      "file": "04 - Sources/Source - FBI Serial 4 Redacted.md",
      "x": -700,
      "y": 480,
      "width": 380,
      "height": 180,
      "color": "7"
    },
    {
      "id": "descA",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Witness A (Serial 4)\n\nDrone pilot, 10-15 flight hours.\n\n==Linear, metallic gray== object; bright white light with visible bands; ==1-2 Blackhawk lengths==; ~5000 ft AGL; ==close==; 5-10 sec; light went out and object vanished.\n\nSelf-attribution: ==unresolved object==.",
      "x": -700,
      "y": 700,
      "width": 380,
      "height": 300,
      "color": "6"
    },
    {
      "id": "wB",
      "type": "file",
      "file": "08 - Witnesses/Witness - LiDAR Test Convoy Witness B.md",
      "x": 160,
      "y": 240,
      "width": 380,
      "height": 200,
      "color": "4"
    },
    {
      "id": "srcB",
      "type": "file",
      "file": "04 - Sources/Source - FBI Serial 5 Redacted.md",
      "x": 160,
      "y": 480,
      "width": 380,
      "height": 180,
      "color": "7"
    },
    {
      "id": "descB",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Witness B (Serial 5)\n\nConvoy lead driver, F-150.\n\n==Point of light== only, no shape detail; stationary then moved right; ==10-20 miles away==; ~10 sec; same size throughout; no vehicle interference.\n\nSelf-attribution: ==probable meteor==.",
      "x": 160,
      "y": 700,
      "width": 380,
      "height": 300,
      "color": "6"
    },
    {
      "id": "takeaway",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Takeaway\n\nTreat ==divergence as the default expectation== for multi-witness transient events, not as evidence of cover-up or of any single witness being unreliable.\n\nWhere witnesses converge, the convergence is informative; where they diverge, the divergence is informative about the difficulty of the observation, not necessarily about the object.",
      "x": -150,
      "y": 1060,
      "width": 660,
      "height": 260,
      "color": "2"
    }
  ],
